Simple Note Pad - Project Outline & Progress Report

Introduction
Simple Note Pad is a lightweight Android application designed for quick note-taking and local data persistence. The project focuses on user-friendly interface design and robust data handling using Android SharedPreferences.

Version Changelog

v1.0 - Week 2 (Previous)

Project Initiation: Defined core app purpose and target audience.

Architecture: Set up the Android Studio environment and basic activity hierarchy.

v1.1 - Week 4 (Previous)

UI Implementation: Developed EditNoteActivity with title and content input fields.

Navigation: Implemented Intent-based transitions between Main and Edit screens.

Styling: Applied AppCompat themes and NoActionBar styles.

v1.2 - Week 5 (Current)

Data Persistence: Integrated SharedPreferences to save user notes to local storage.

Bug Fixes: Resolved Theme.AppCompat compatibility issues causing app crashes.

UI Refinement: Optimized button layouts and added Toast notifications for save confirmation.

v1.3 - Weeks 6 to 8 (Future)

List View: Transition to a list-based display for multiple saved notes.

CRUD Operations: Add functionality to delete and edit existing notes.

Final Presentation: Prepare technical documentation and investor pitch deck.

Project Details

Platform: Android API 36 (Java)

Frontend: XML Layouts (Material3/AppCompat)

Backend: SharedPreferences for persistence
